<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 1:1-54</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="54">
<p class="l"><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Adam,<br><span class="p">Seth,</span><br><span class="p">E&acute;nosh,</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Ke&acute;nan,<br><span class="p">Ma&middot;hal&acute;a&middot;lel,</span><br><span class="p">Ja&acute;red,</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">E&acute;noch,<br><span class="p">Me&middot;thu&acute;se&middot;lah,</span><br><span class="p">La&acute;mech,</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Noah,<br><span class="p">Shem, Ham and Ja&acute;pheth.</span></span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">The sons of Ja&acute;pheth were Go&acute;mer and Ma&acute;gog and Ma&acute;da&middot;i and Ja&acute;van and Tu&acute;bal and Me&acute;shech and Ti&acute;ras.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And the sons of Go&acute;mer were Ash&acute;ke&middot;naz and Ri&acute;phath and To&middot;gar&acute;mah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And the sons of Ja&acute;van were E&middot;li&acute;shah and Tar&acute;shish, Kit&acute;tim and Ro&acute;da&middot;nim.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">The sons of Ham were Cush and Miz&acute;ra&middot;im, Put and Ca&acute;naan.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And the sons of Cush were Se&acute;ba and Hav&acute;i&middot;lah and Sab&acute;tah and Ra&acute;a&middot;mah and Sab&acute;te&middot;ca.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs9-2">And the sons of Ra&acute;a&middot;mah were She&acute;ba and De&acute;dan.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And Cush himself became father to Nim&acute;rod. He it was that made the start in becoming a mighty one in the earth.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">As for Miz&acute;ra&middot;im, he became father to Lu&acute;dim and An&acute;a&middot;mim and Le&middot;ha&acute;bim and Naph&middot;tu&acute;him</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">and Path&middot;ru&acute;sim and Cas&middot;lu&acute;him (from among whom the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines went forth) and Caph&acute;to&middot;rim.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">As for Ca&acute;naan, he became father to Si&acute;don his firstborn and Heth</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">and the Jeb&acute;u&middot;site and the Am&acute;or&middot;ite and the Gir&acute;ga&middot;shite</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">and the Hi&acute;vite and the Ark&acute;ite and the Si&acute;nite</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">and the Ar&acute;vad&middot;ite and the Zem&acute;a&middot;rite and the Ha&acute;math&middot;ite.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">The sons of Shem were E&acute;lam and As&acute;shur and Ar&middot;pach&acute;shad and Lud and A&acute;ram,</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs17-2">And Uz and Hul and Ge&acute;ther and Mash.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">As for Ar&middot;pach&acute;shad, he became father to She&acute;lah, and She&acute;lah himself became father to E&acute;ber.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And to E&acute;ber two sons were born. The name of the one was Pe&acute;leg, because in his days the earth was divided; and the name of his brother was Jok&acute;tan.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">As for Jok&acute;tan, he became father to Al&middot;mo&acute;dad and She&acute;leph and Ha&middot;zar&middot;ma&acute;veth and Je&acute;rah</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">and Ha&middot;do&acute;ram and U&acute;zal and Dik&acute;lah</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">and O&acute;bal and A&middot;bim&acute;a&middot;el and She&acute;ba</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">and O&acute;phir and Hav&acute;i&middot;lah and Jo&acute;bab; all these were the sons of Jok&acute;tan.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">Shem,<br><span class="z">Ar&middot;pach&acute;shad,</span><br><span class="z">She&acute;lah,</span></span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">E&acute;ber,<br><span class="z">Pe&acute;leg,</span><br><span class="z">Re&acute;u,</span></span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">Se&acute;rug,<br><span class="z">Na&acute;hor,</span><br><span class="z">Te&acute;rah,</span></span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">A&acute;bram, that is to say, Abraham.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">The sons of Abraham were Isaac and Ish&acute;ma&middot;el.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">These are their family origins: Ish&acute;ma&middot;el’s firstborn Ne&middot;ba&acute;ioth and Ke&acute;dar and Ad&acute;be&middot;el and Mib&acute;sam,</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">Mish&acute;ma and Du&acute;mah, Mas&acute;sa, Ha&acute;dad and Te&acute;ma,</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">Je&acute;tur, Na&acute;phish and Ked&acute;e&middot;mah. These were the sons of Ish&acute;ma&middot;el.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">As for the sons of Ke&middot;tu&acute;rah, Abraham’s concubine, she gave birth to Zim&acute;ran and Jok&acute;shan and Me&acute;dan and Mid&acute;i&middot;an and Ish&acute;bak and Shu&acute;ah.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs32-2">And the sons of Jok&acute;shan were She&acute;ba and De&acute;dan.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">And the sons of Mid&acute;i&middot;an were E&acute;phah and E&acute;pher and Ha&acute;noch and A&middot;bi&acute;da and El&middot;da&acute;ah.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs33-2">All these were the sons of Ke&middot;tu&acute;rah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">And Abraham came to be father to Isaac. The sons of Isaac were E&acute;sau and Israel.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">The sons of E&acute;sau were El&acute;i&middot;phaz, Reu&acute;el and Je&acute;ush and Ja&acute;lam and Ko&acute;rah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">The sons of El&acute;i&middot;phaz were Te&acute;man and O&acute;mar, Ze&acute;pho and Ga&acute;tam, Ke&acute;naz and Tim&acute;na and Am&acute;a&middot;lek.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">The sons of Reu&acute;el were Na&acute;hath, Ze&acute;rah, Sham&acute;mah and Miz&acute;zah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">And the sons of Se&acute;ir were Lo&acute;tan and Sho&acute;bal and Zib&acute;e&middot;on and A&acute;nah and Di&acute;shon and E&acute;zer and Di&acute;shan.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">And the sons of Lo&acute;tan were Ho&acute;ri and Ho&acute;mam. And Lo&acute;tan’s sister was Tim&acute;na.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">The sons of Sho&acute;bal were Al&acute;van and Man&acute;a&middot;hath and E&acute;bal, She&acute;pho and O&acute;nam.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs40-2">And the sons of Zib&acute;e&middot;on were A&acute;iah and A&acute;nah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">The sons of A&acute;nah were Di&acute;shon.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs41-2">And the sons of Di&acute;shon were Hem&acute;dan and Esh&acute;ban and Ith&acute;ran and Che&acute;ran.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">The sons of E&acute;zer were Bil&acute;han and Za&acute;a&middot;van and A&acute;kan.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs42-2">The sons of Di&acute;shan were Uz and A&acute;ran.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">And these are the kings that reigned in the land of E&acute;dom before any king reigned over the sons of Israel: Be&acute;la the son of Be&acute;or, the name of whose city was Din&acute;ha&middot;bah.</span> <a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">Eventually Be&acute;la died, and Jo&acute;bab the son of Ze&acute;rah from Boz&acute;rah began to reign in place of him.</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">Eventually Jo&acute;bab died, and Hu&acute;sham from the land of the Te&acute;man&middot;ites began to reign in place of him.</span> <a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">Eventually Hu&acute;sham died, and Ha&acute;dad the son of Be&acute;dad, who defeated Mid&acute;i&middot;an in the field of Mo&acute;ab, began to reign in place of him. And the name of his city was A&acute;vith.</span> <a name="bk47" class="vsAnchor">47</a>
       <span id="vs47">Eventually Ha&acute;dad died, and Sam&acute;lah from Mas&middot;re&acute;kah began to reign in place of him.</span> <a name="bk48" class="vsAnchor">48</a>
       <span id="vs48">Eventually Sam&acute;lah died, and Sha&acute;ul from Re&middot;ho&acute;both by the River began to reign in place of him.</span> <a name="bk49" class="vsAnchor">49</a>
       <span id="vs49">Eventually Sha&acute;ul died, and Ba&acute;al-ha&acute;nan the son of Ach&acute;bor began to reign in place of him.</span> <a name="bk50" class="vsAnchor">50</a>
       <span id="vs50">Eventually Ba&acute;al-ha&acute;nan died, and Ha&acute;dad began to reign in place of him; and the name of his city was Pa&acute;u, and the name of his wife was Me&middot;het&acute;a&middot;bel, the daughter of Ma&acute;tred, the daughter of Me&acute;za&middot;hab.</span> <a name="bk51" class="vsAnchor">51</a>
       <span id="vs51">Eventually Ha&acute;dad died.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs51-2">And the sheiks of E&acute;dom came to be sheik Tim&acute;na, sheik Al&acute;vah, sheik Je&acute;theth,</span> <a name="bk52" class="vsAnchor">52</a>
       <span id="vs52">sheik O&middot;hol&middot;i&middot;ba&acute;mah, sheik E&acute;lah, sheik Pi&acute;non,</span> <a name="bk53" class="vsAnchor">53</a>
       <span id="vs53">sheik Ke&acute;naz, sheik Te&acute;man, sheik Mib&acute;zar,</span> <a name="bk54" class="vsAnchor">54</a>
       <span id="vs54">sheik Mag&acute;di&middot;el, sheik I&acute;ram. These were the sheiks of E&acute;dom.</span>
</p>
</form>

