<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 2:1-55</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="55">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">These were the sons of Israel: Reu&acute;ben, Sim&acute;e&middot;on, Le&acute;vi and Judah, Is&acute;sa&middot;char and Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun,</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Dan, Joseph and Benjamin, Naph&acute;ta&middot;li, Gad and Ash&acute;er.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">The sons of Judah were Er and O&acute;nan and She&acute;lah. The three were born to him from Shu&acute;a’s daughter, the Ca&acute;naan&middot;it&middot;ess. And Er the firstborn of Judah came to be bad in the eyes of Jehovah, so that he put him to death.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And Ta&acute;mar his daughter-in-law it was that bore to him Pe&acute;rez and Ze&acute;rah. All the sons of Judah were five.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">The sons of Pe&acute;rez were Hez&acute;ron and Ha&acute;mul.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And the sons of Ze&acute;rah were Zim&acute;ri and E&acute;than and He&acute;man and Cal&acute;col and Da&acute;ra. There were five of them in all.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And the sons of Car&acute;mi were A&acute;char the bringer of ostracism upon Israel, who committed an act of unfaithfulness respecting the thing devoted to destruction.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And the sons of E&acute;than were Az&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And the sons of Hez&acute;ron that were born to him were Je&middot;rah&acute;me&middot;el and Ram and Che&middot;lu&acute;bai.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">As for Ram, he became father to Am&middot;min&acute;a&middot;dab. Am&middot;min&acute;a&middot;dab, in turn, became father to Nah&acute;shon the chieftain of the sons of Judah.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Nah&acute;shon, in turn, became father to Sal&acute;ma. Sal&acute;ma, in turn, became father to Bo&acute;az.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Bo&acute;az, in turn, became father to O&acute;bed. O&acute;bed, in turn, became father to Jes&acute;se.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Jes&acute;se, in turn, became father to his firstborn E&middot;li&acute;ab, and A&middot;bin&acute;a&middot;dab the second, and Shim&acute;e&middot;a the third,</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">Ne&middot;than&acute;el the fourth, Rad&acute;dai the fifth,</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">O&acute;zem the sixth, David the seventh.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And their sisters were Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah and Ab&acute;i&middot;gail; and the sons of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah were A&middot;bish&acute;ai and Jo&acute;ab and As&acute;a&middot;hel, three.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">As for Ab&acute;i&middot;gail, she gave birth to A&middot;ma&acute;sa; and the father of A&middot;ma&acute;sa was Je&acute;ther the Ish&acute;ma&middot;el&middot;ite.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">As for Ca&acute;leb the son of Hez&acute;ron, he became father to sons by A&middot;zu&acute;bah his wife and by Jer&acute;i&middot;oth; and these were her sons: Je&acute;sher and Sho&acute;bab and Ar&acute;don.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">Eventually A&middot;zu&acute;bah died. So Ca&acute;leb took to himself Eph&acute;rath, who in time bore Hur to him.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">Hur, in turn, became father to U&acute;ri. U&acute;ri, in turn, became father to Bez&acute;al&middot;el.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And afterward Hez&acute;ron had relations with the daughter of Ma&acute;chir the father of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad. And he himself took her when he was sixty years old, but she bore Se&acute;gub to him.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">Se&acute;gub, in turn, became father to Ja&acute;ir, who came to have twenty-three cities in the land of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">Later Gesh&acute;ur and Syria took Hav&acute;voth-ja&acute;ir from them, with Ke&acute;nath and its dependent towns, sixty cities. All these were the sons of Ma&acute;chir the father of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And after the death of Hez&acute;ron in Ca&acute;leb-eph&acute;ra&middot;thah, with A&middot;bi&acute;jah being the wife of Hez&acute;ron, she then bore him Ash&acute;hur the father of Te&middot;ko&acute;a.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And the sons of Je&middot;rah&acute;me&middot;el the firstborn of Hez&acute;ron were Ram the firstborn and Bu&acute;nah and O&acute;ren and O&acute;zem, A&middot;hi&acute;jah.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And Je&middot;rah&acute;me&middot;el came to have another wife, whose name was At&acute;a&middot;rah. She was the mother of O&acute;nam.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And the sons of Ram the firstborn of Je&middot;rah&acute;me&middot;el came to be Ma&acute;az and Ja&acute;min and E&acute;ker.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And the sons of O&acute;nam came to be Sham&acute;mai and Ja&acute;da. And the sons of Sham&acute;mai were Na&acute;dab and A&middot;bi&acute;shur.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And the name of A&middot;bi&acute;shur’s wife was Ab&acute;i&middot;ha&middot;il, who in time bore him Ah&acute;ban and Mo&acute;lid.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">And the sons of Na&acute;dab were Se&acute;led and Ap&acute;pa&middot;im. But Se&acute;led died without sons.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And the sons of Ap&acute;pa&middot;im were Ish&acute;i. And the sons of Ish&acute;i were She&acute;shan; and the sons of She&acute;shan, Ah&acute;lai.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And the sons of Ja&acute;da the brother of Sham&acute;mai were Je&acute;ther and Jon&acute;a&middot;than. But Je&acute;ther died without sons.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">And the sons of Jon&acute;a&middot;than were Pe&acute;leth and Za&acute;za. These became the sons of Je&middot;rah&acute;me&middot;el.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">And She&acute;shan came to have no sons, but daughters. Now She&acute;shan had an Egyptian servant whose name was Jar&acute;ha.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">So She&acute;shan gave his daughter to Jar&acute;ha his servant as a wife, who in time bore him At&acute;tai.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">At&acute;tai, in turn, became father to Nathan. Nathan, in turn, became father to Za&acute;bad.</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Za&acute;bad, in turn, became father to Eph&acute;lal. Eph&acute;lal, in turn, became father to O&acute;bed.</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">O&acute;bed, in turn, became father to Je&acute;hu. Je&acute;hu, in turn, became father to Az&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah.</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">Az&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah, in turn, became father to He&acute;lez. He&acute;lez, in turn, became father to El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;sah.</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;sah, in turn, became father to Sis&acute;mai. Sis&acute;mai, in turn, became father to Shal&acute;lum.</span> <a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">Shal&acute;lum, in turn, became father to Jek&middot;a&middot;mi&acute;ah. Jek&middot;a&middot;mi&acute;ah, in turn, became father to E&middot;lish&acute;a&middot;ma.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">And the sons of Ca&acute;leb the brother of Je&middot;rah&acute;me&middot;el were Me&acute;sha his firstborn, who was the father of Ziph, and the sons of Ma&middot;re&acute;shah the father of He&acute;bron.</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">And the sons of He&acute;bron were Ko&acute;rah and Tap&acute;pu&middot;ah and Re&acute;kem and She&acute;ma.</span> <a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">She&acute;ma, in turn, became father to Ra&acute;ham the father of Jor&acute;ke&middot;am. Re&acute;kem, in turn, became father to Sham&acute;mai.</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">And the son of Sham&acute;mai was Ma&acute;on; and Ma&acute;on was the father of Beth-zur.</span> <a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">As for E&acute;phah the concubine of Ca&acute;leb, she gave birth to Ha&acute;ran and Mo&acute;za and Ga&acute;zez. As for Ha&acute;ran, he became father to Ga&acute;zez.</span> <a name="bk47" class="vsAnchor">47</a>
       <span id="vs47">And the sons of Jah&acute;dai were Re&acute;gem and Jo&acute;tham and Ge&acute;shan and Pel&acute;et and E&acute;phah and Sha&acute;aph.</span> <a name="bk48" class="vsAnchor">48</a>
       <span id="vs48">As for Ca&acute;leb’s concubine Ma&acute;a&middot;cah, she gave birth to She&acute;ber and Tir&acute;ha&middot;nah.</span> <a name="bk49" class="vsAnchor">49</a>
       <span id="vs49">In time she bore Sha&acute;aph the father of Mad&middot;man&acute;nah, She&acute;va the father of Mach&middot;be&acute;nah and the father of Gib&acute;e&middot;a. And Ca&acute;leb’s daughter was Ach&acute;sah.</span> <a name="bk50" class="vsAnchor">50</a>
       <span id="vs50">These became the sons of Ca&acute;leb.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs50-2">The sons of Hur the firstborn of Eph&acute;ra&middot;thah: Sho&acute;bal the father of Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim,</span> <a name="bk51" class="vsAnchor">51</a>
       <span id="vs51">Sal&acute;ma the father of Beth&acute;le&middot;hem, Ha&acute;reph the father of Beth-ga&acute;der.</span> <a name="bk52" class="vsAnchor">52</a>
       <span id="vs52">And Sho&acute;bal the father of Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim came to have sons: Ha&middot;ro&acute;eh, half of the Me&middot;nu&acute;hoth.</span> <a name="bk53" class="vsAnchor">53</a>
       <span id="vs53">And the families of Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim were the Ith&acute;rites and the Pu&acute;thites and the Shu&acute;math&middot;ites and the Mish&acute;ra&middot;ites. It was from these that the Zo&acute;rath&middot;ites and the Esh&acute;ta&middot;ol&middot;ites came out.</span> <a name="bk54" class="vsAnchor">54</a>
       <span id="vs54">The sons of Sal&acute;ma were Beth&acute;le&middot;hem and the Ne&middot;toph&acute;a&middot;thites, At&acute;roth-beth-jo&acute;ab and half of the Man&middot;a&middot;ha&acute;thites, the Zor&acute;ites.</span> <a name="bk55" class="vsAnchor">55</a>
       <span id="vs55">And the families of the scribes dwelling at Ja&acute;bez were the Ti&acute;rath&middot;ites, the Shim&acute;e&middot;ath&middot;ites, the Su&acute;cath&middot;ites. These were the Ken&acute;ites that came from Ham&acute;math the father of the house of Re&acute;chab.</span>
</p>
</form>

