<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 4:1-43</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="43">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">The sons of Judah were Pe&acute;rez, Hez&acute;ron and Car&acute;mi and Hur and Sho&acute;bal.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">As for Re&middot;a&acute;iah the son of Sho&acute;bal, he became father to Ja&acute;hath; Ja&acute;hath, in turn, became father to A&middot;hu&acute;mai and La&acute;had. These were the families of the Zo&acute;rath&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And these were [the sons of] the father of E&acute;tam: Jez&acute;re&middot;el and Ish&acute;ma and Id&acute;bash, (and the name of their sister was Haz&middot;ze&middot;lel&middot;po&acute;ni,)</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">and Pe&middot;nu&acute;el the father of Ge&acute;dor and E&acute;zer the father of Hu&acute;shah. These were the sons of Hur the firstborn of Eph&acute;ra&middot;thah the father of Beth&acute;le&middot;hem.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And Ash&acute;hur the father of Te&middot;ko&acute;a came to have two wives, He&acute;lah and Na&acute;a&middot;rah.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">In time Na&acute;a&middot;rah bore to him A&middot;huz&acute;zam and He&acute;pher and Te&acute;me&middot;ni and Ha&middot;a&middot;hash&acute;ta&middot;ri. These were the sons of Na&acute;a&middot;rah.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And the sons of He&acute;lah were Ze&acute;reth, Iz&acute;har and Eth&acute;nan.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">As for Koz, he became father to A&acute;nub and Zo&middot;be&acute;bah and the families of A&middot;har&acute;hel the son of Ha&acute;rum.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And Ja&acute;bez came to be more honorable than his brothers; and it was his mother that called his name Ja&acute;bez, saying: “I have given him birth in pain.”</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And Ja&acute;bez began to call upon the God of Israel, saying: “If you will without fail bless me and actually enlarge my territory and your hand really proves to be with me, and you really preserve [me] from calamity, that it may not hurt me,—” Accordingly God brought [to pass] what he had asked.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">As for Che&acute;lub the brother of Shu&acute;hah, he became father to Me&acute;hir, who was the father of Esh&acute;ton.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Esh&acute;ton, in turn, became father to Beth-ra&acute;pha and Pa&middot;se&acute;ah and Te&middot;hin&acute;nah the father of Ir-na&acute;hash. These were the men of Re&acute;cah.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And the sons of Ke&acute;naz were Oth&acute;ni&middot;el and Se&middot;rai&acute;ah, and the sons of Oth&acute;ni&middot;el, Ha&acute;thath.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">As for Me&middot;o&acute;no&middot;thai, he became father to Oph&acute;rah. As for Se&middot;rai&acute;ah, he became father to Jo&acute;ab the father of Ge-har&acute;a&middot;shim; for craftsmen are what they became.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And the sons of Ca&acute;leb the son of Je&middot;phun&acute;neh were I&acute;ru, E&acute;lah and Na&acute;am; and the sons of E&acute;lah, Ke&acute;naz.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And the sons of Je&middot;hal&acute;le&middot;lel were Ziph and Zi&acute;phah, Tir&acute;i&middot;a and As&acute;a&middot;rel.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And the sons of Ez&acute;rah were Je&acute;ther and Me&acute;red and E&acute;pher and Ja&acute;lon; and she got to conceive Mir&acute;i&middot;am and Sham&acute;mai and Ish&acute;bah the father of Esh&middot;te&middot;mo&acute;a.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">As for his Jewish wife, she gave birth to Je&acute;red the father of Ge&acute;dor and He&acute;ber the father of So&acute;co and Je&middot;ku&acute;thi&middot;el the father of Za&middot;no&acute;ah. And these were the sons of Bi&middot;thi&acute;ah the daughter of Phar&acute;aoh, whom Me&acute;red took.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And the sons of Ho&middot;di&acute;ah’s wife, the sister of Na&acute;ham, were the father of Kei&acute;lah the Gar&acute;mite and Esh&middot;te&middot;mo&acute;a the Ma&middot;ac&acute;a&middot;thite.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And the sons of Shi&acute;mon were Am&acute;non and Rin&acute;nah, Ben-ha&acute;nan and Ti&acute;lon. And the sons of Ish&acute;i were Zo&acute;heth and Ben-zo&acute;heth.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">The sons of She&acute;lah the son of Judah were Er the father of Le&acute;cah and La&acute;a&middot;dah the father of Ma&middot;re&acute;shah and the families of the house of the workers of fine fabric of the house of Ash&middot;be&acute;a;</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">and Jo&acute;kim and the men of Co&middot;ze&acute;ba and Jo&acute;ash and Sa&acute;raph, who became owners of Mo&acute;ab&middot;ite wives, and Jash&acute;u&middot;bi-le&acute;hem. And the sayings are of old tradition.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">They were the potters and the inhabitants of Ne&middot;ta&acute;im and Ge&middot;de&acute;rah. It was with the king in his work that they dwelt there.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">The sons of Sim&acute;e&middot;on were Nem&acute;u&middot;el and Ja&acute;min, Ja&acute;rib, Ze&acute;rah, Sha&acute;ul,</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">Shal&acute;lum his son, Mib&acute;sam his son, Mish&acute;ma his son.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And the sons of Mish&acute;ma were Ham&acute;mu&middot;el his son, Zac&acute;cur his son, Shim&acute;e&middot;i his son.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And Shim&acute;e&middot;i had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers did not have many sons, and none of their families had as many as the sons of Judah.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And they continued to dwell in Be&acute;er-she&acute;ba and Mo&middot;la&acute;dah and Ha&acute;zar-shu&acute;al</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">and in Bil&acute;hah and in E&acute;zem and in To&acute;lad</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">and in Be&middot;thu&acute;el and in Hor&acute;mah and in Zik&acute;lag</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">and in Beth-mar&acute;ca&middot;both and in Ha&acute;zar-su&acute;sim and in Beth-bir&acute;i and in Sha&acute;a&middot;ra&acute;im. These were their cities down till David reigned.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And their settlements were E&acute;tam and A&acute;in, Rim&acute;mon and To&acute;chen and A&acute;shan, five cities.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">And all their settlements that were all around these cities were as far as Ba&acute;al. These were their dwelling places and their genealogical enrollments for them.</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">And Me&middot;sho&acute;bab and Jam&acute;lech and Jo&acute;shah the son of Am&middot;a&middot;zi&acute;ah,</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">and Joel and Je&acute;hu the son of Josh&middot;i&middot;bi&acute;ah the son of Se&middot;rai&acute;ah the son of As&acute;i&middot;el,</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">and Eli&middot;o&middot;e&acute;nai and Ja&middot;a&middot;ko&acute;bah and Jesh&middot;o&middot;hai&acute;ah and A&middot;sai&acute;ah and Ad&acute;i&middot;el and Je&middot;sim&acute;i&middot;el and Be&middot;nai&acute;ah,</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">and Zi&acute;za the son of Shi&acute;phi the son of Al&acute;lon the son of Je&middot;da&acute;iah the son of Shim&acute;ri the son of She&middot;mai&acute;ah.</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">These who came in by names were the chieftains among their families, and the household itself of their forefathers increased in multitude.</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">And they proceeded to go to the entryway of Ge&acute;dor, clear to the east of the valley, to look for pasturage for their flocks.</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">Eventually they found fat and good pasturage, and the land was quite wide and having no disturbance but at ease; for those dwelling there in former times were of Ham.</span> <a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">And these written down by [their] names proceeded to come in in the days of Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah the king of Judah and strike down the tents of the Ham&acute;ites and the Me&middot;u&acute;nim that were to be found there, so that they devoted them to destruction down to this day; and they began to dwell in their place, because there was pasturage for their flocks there.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">And from them there were some of the sons of Sim&acute;e&middot;on that went to Mount Se&acute;ir, five hundred men, with Pel&middot;a&middot;ti&acute;ah and Ne&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah and Re&middot;pha&acute;iah and Uz&acute;zi&middot;el the sons of Ish&acute;i at their head.</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">And they proceeded to strike down the remnant that had escaped of Am&acute;a&middot;lek, and they continued to dwell there down to this day.</span>
</p>
</form>

