<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 7:1-40</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="40">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Now the sons of Is&acute;sa&middot;char were To&acute;la and Pu&acute;ah, Ja&acute;shub and Shim&acute;ron, four.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And the sons of To&acute;la were Uz&acute;zi and Re&middot;pha&acute;iah and Je&acute;ri&middot;el and Jah&acute;mai and Ib&acute;sam and She&middot;mu&acute;el, heads of the house of their forefathers. Of To&acute;la there were valiant, mighty men, by their descendants. Their number in the days of David was twenty-two thousand six hundred.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And the sons of Uz&acute;zi were Iz&middot;ra&middot;hi&acute;ah; and the sons of Iz&middot;ra&middot;hi&acute;ah were Mi&acute;cha&middot;el and O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah and Joel, Is&middot;shi&acute;ah, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;, five, all of them being heads.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And with them by their descendants, according to the house of their forefathers, there were troops of the army for war, thirty-six thousand, for they had many wives and sons.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And their brothers of all the families of Is&acute;sa&middot;char were valiant, mighty men, eighty-seven thousand by the genealogical enrollment of them all.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">[The sons of] Benjamin were Be&acute;la and Be&acute;cher and Je&middot;di&acute;a&middot;el, three.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And the sons of Be&acute;la were Ez&acute;bon and Uz&acute;zi and Uz&acute;zi&middot;el and Jer&acute;i&middot;moth and I&acute;ri, five, heads of the house of their forefathers, valiant, mighty men; and their genealogical enrollment was twenty-two thousand and thirty-four.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And the sons of Be&acute;cher were Ze&middot;mi&acute;rah and Jo&acute;ash and E&middot;li&middot;e&acute;zer and Eli&middot;o&middot;e&acute;nai and Om&acute;ri and Jer&acute;e&middot;moth and A&middot;bi&acute;jah and An&acute;a&middot;thoth and Al&acute;e&middot;meth, all these the sons of Be&acute;cher.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And their genealogical enrollment by their descendants as respects the heads of the house of their forefathers, valiant, mighty men, was twenty thousand two hundred.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And the sons of Je&middot;di&acute;a&middot;el were Bil&acute;han; and the sons of Bil&acute;han were Je&acute;ush and Benjamin and E&acute;hud and Che&middot;na&acute;a&middot;nah and Ze&acute;than and Tar&acute;shish and A&middot;hish&acute;a&middot;har.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">All these were the sons of Je&middot;di&acute;a&middot;el, according to the heads of their forefathers, valiant, mighty men, seventeen thousand two hundred going out to the army for war.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And the Shup&acute;pim and the Hup&acute;pim were the sons of Ir; the Hu&acute;shim were the sons of A&acute;her.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">The sons of Naph&acute;ta&middot;li were Jah&acute;zi&middot;el and Gu&acute;ni and Je&acute;zer and Shal&acute;lum, the sons of Bil&acute;hah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">The sons of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh were As&acute;ri&middot;el, whom his Syrian concubine bore. (She bore Ma&acute;chir the father of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And Ma&acute;chir himself took a wife for Hup&acute;pim and for Shup&acute;pim, and the name of his sister was Ma&acute;a&middot;cah.) And the name of the second was Ze&middot;lo&acute;phe&middot;had, but Ze&middot;lo&acute;phe&middot;had came to have daughters.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">In time Ma&acute;a&middot;cah, Ma&acute;chir’s wife, bore a son and called his name Pe&acute;resh; and the name of his brother was She&acute;resh; and his sons were U&acute;lam and Re&acute;kem.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And the sons of U&acute;lam were Be&acute;dan. These were the sons of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad the son of Ma&acute;chir the son of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And his sister was Ham&middot;mo&acute;le&middot;cheth. She gave birth to Ish&acute;hod and Abi-e&acute;zer and Mah&acute;lah.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And the sons of She&middot;mi&acute;da came to be A&middot;hi&acute;an and She&acute;chem and Lik&acute;hi and A&middot;ni&acute;am.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And the sons of E&acute;phra&middot;im were Shu&acute;the&middot;lah and Be&acute;red his son and Ta&acute;hath his son and E&middot;le&middot;a&acute;dah his son and Ta&acute;hath his son,</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">and Za&acute;bad his son and Shu&acute;the&middot;lah his son and E&acute;zer and E&acute;le&middot;ad. And the men of Gath that were born in the land killed them because they came down to take their livestock.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And E&acute;phra&middot;im their father carried on mourning for many days, and his brothers kept coming in to comfort him.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">Afterward he had relations with his wife, so that she became pregnant and gave birth to a son. But he called his name Be&middot;ri&acute;ah, because it was with calamity that she happened to be in his house.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And his daughter was She&acute;e&middot;rah, and she got to build Beth-ho&acute;ron, the lower and the upper, and Uz&acute;zen-she&acute;e&middot;rah.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And there was Re&acute;phah his son, and Re&acute;sheph, and Te&acute;lah his son, and Ta&acute;han his son,</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">La&acute;dan his son, Am&middot;mi&acute;hud his son, E&middot;lish&acute;a&middot;ma his son,</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">Nun his son, Je&middot;hosh&acute;u&middot;a his son.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And their possession and their dwelling places were Beth&acute;el and its dependent towns and, to the east, Na&acute;a&middot;ran and, to the west, Ge&acute;zer and its dependent towns, and She&acute;chem and its dependent towns clear to Ga&acute;za and its dependent towns;</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">and by the side of the sons of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh Beth-she&acute;an and its dependent towns, Ta&acute;a&middot;nach and its dependent towns, Me&middot;gid&acute;do and its dependent towns, Dor and its dependent towns. In these the sons of Joseph the son of Israel dwelt.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">The sons of Ash&acute;er were Im&acute;nah and Ish&acute;vah and Ish&acute;vi and Be&middot;ri&acute;ah; and Se&acute;rah was their sister.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And the sons of Be&middot;ri&acute;ah were He&acute;ber and Mal&acute;chi&middot;el, who was the father of Bir&acute;za&middot;ith.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">As for He&acute;ber, he became father to Japh&acute;let and Sho&acute;mer and Ho&acute;tham, and to Shu&acute;a their sister.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">And the sons of Japh&acute;let were Pa&acute;sach and Bim&acute;hal and Ash&acute;vath. These were the sons of Japh&acute;let.</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">And the sons of She&acute;mer were A&acute;hi and Roh&acute;gah, Je&middot;hub&acute;bah and A&acute;ram.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">And the sons of He&acute;lem his brother were Zo&acute;phah and Im&acute;na and She&acute;lesh and A&acute;mal.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">The sons of Zo&acute;phah were Su&acute;ah and Har&acute;ne&middot;pher and Shu&acute;al and Be&acute;ri and Im&acute;rah,</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Be&acute;zer and Hod and Sham&acute;ma and Shil&acute;shah and Ith&acute;ran and Be&middot;e&acute;ra.</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">And the sons of Je&acute;ther were Je&middot;phun&acute;neh and Pis&acute;pah and A&acute;ra.</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">And the sons of Ul&acute;la were A&acute;rah and Han&acute;ni&middot;el and Ri&middot;zi&acute;a.</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">All these were the sons of Ash&acute;er, heads of the house of the forefathers, select, valiant, mighty men, heads of the chieftains; and their genealogical enrollment was in the army in the war. Their number was twenty-six thousand men.</span>
</p>
</form>

