<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 8:1-40</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="40">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">As for Benjamin, he became father to Be&acute;la his firstborn, Ash&acute;bel the second and A&middot;har&acute;ah the third,</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">No&acute;hah the fourth and Ra&acute;pha the fifth.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And Be&acute;la came to have sons, Ad&acute;dar and Ge&acute;ra and A&middot;bi&acute;hud,</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">and Ab&middot;i&middot;shu&acute;a and Na&acute;a&middot;man and A&middot;ho&acute;ah,</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">and Ge&acute;ra and She&middot;phu&acute;phan and Hu&acute;ram.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And these were the sons of E&acute;hud. These were the heads of [the houses of] forefathers belonging to the inhabitants of Ge&acute;ba, and they proceeded to take them into exile at Man&acute;a&middot;hath.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And Na&acute;a&middot;man and A&middot;hi&acute;jah; and Ge&acute;ra—he was the one that took them into exile, and he became father to Uz&acute;za and A&middot;hi&acute;hud.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">As for Sha&middot;ha&middot;ra&acute;im, he became father to [children] in the field of Mo&acute;ab after he sent them away. Hu&acute;shim and Ba&acute;a&middot;ra were his wives.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And by Ho&acute;desh his wife he came to be father to Jo&acute;bab and Zib&acute;i&middot;a and Me&acute;sha and Mal&acute;cam,</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">and Je&acute;uz and Sa&middot;chi&acute;a and Mir&acute;mah. These were his sons, heads of [the houses of] forefathers.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And by Hu&acute;shim he became father to A&middot;bi&acute;tub and El&middot;pa&acute;al.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And the sons of El&middot;pa&acute;al were E&acute;ber and Mi&acute;sham and She&acute;med, who built O&acute;no and Lod and its dependent towns,</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">and Be&middot;ri&acute;ah and She&acute;ma. These were heads of [the houses of] forefathers, belonging to the inhabitants of Ai&acute;ja&middot;lon. These were the ones that chased away the inhabitants of Gath.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And [there were] A&middot;hi&acute;o, Sha&acute;shak and Jer&acute;e&middot;moth,</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">and Zeb&middot;a&middot;di&acute;ah and A&acute;rad and E&acute;der,</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">and Mi&acute;cha&middot;el and Ish&acute;pah and Jo&acute;ha, the sons of Be&middot;ri&acute;ah,</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">and Zeb&middot;a&middot;di&acute;ah and Me&middot;shul&acute;lam and Hiz&acute;ki and He&acute;ber,</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">and Ish&acute;me&middot;rai and Iz&middot;li&acute;ah and Jo&acute;bab, the sons of El&middot;pa&acute;al,</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">and Ja&acute;kim and Zich&acute;ri and Zab&acute;di,</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">and E&middot;li&middot;e&acute;nai and Zil&acute;le&middot;thai and E&acute;li&middot;el,</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">and A&middot;dai&acute;ah and Be&middot;ra&acute;iah and Shim&acute;rath, the sons of Shim&acute;e&middot;i,</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">and Ish&acute;pan and E&acute;ber and E&acute;li&middot;el,</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">and Ab&acute;don and Zich&acute;ri and Ha&acute;nan,</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">and Han&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah and E&acute;lam and An&middot;tho&middot;thi&acute;jah,</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">and Iph&middot;de&acute;iah and Pe&middot;nu&acute;el, the sons of Sha&acute;shak,</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">and Sham&acute;she&middot;rai and She&middot;ha&middot;ri&acute;ah and Ath&middot;a&middot;li&acute;ah,</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">and Ja&middot;a&middot;re&middot;shi&acute;ah and E&middot;li&acute;jah and Zich&acute;ri, the sons of Je&middot;ro&acute;ham.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">These were heads of [the houses of] forefathers by their descendants, headmen. These were the ones that dwelt in Jerusalem.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And it was in Gib&acute;e&middot;on that the father of Gib&acute;e&middot;on, [Je&middot;i&acute;el,] dwelt, and his wife’s name was Ma&acute;a&middot;cah.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">And his son, the firstborn, was Ab&acute;don, and Zur and Kish and Ba&acute;al and Na&acute;dab,</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">and Ge&acute;dor and A&middot;hi&acute;o and Ze&acute;cher.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">As for Mik&acute;loth, he became father to Shim&acute;e&middot;ah. And these really were the ones that dwelt in front of their brothers in Jerusalem along with brothers of theirs.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">As for Ner, he became father to Kish; Kish, in turn, became father to Saul; Saul, in turn, became father to Jon&acute;a&middot;than and Mal&acute;chi-shu&acute;a and A&middot;bin&acute;a&middot;dab and Esh&middot;ba&acute;al.</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">And Jon&acute;a&middot;than’s son was Mer&acute;ib-ba&acute;al. As for Mer&acute;ib-ba&acute;al, he became father to Mi&acute;cah.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">And the sons of Mi&acute;cah were Pi&acute;thon and Mel&acute;ech and Ta&middot;re&acute;a and A&acute;haz.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">As for A&acute;haz, he became father to Je&middot;ho&acute;ad&middot;dah; Je&middot;ho&acute;ad&middot;dah, in turn, became father to Al&acute;e&middot;meth and Az&acute;ma&middot;veth and Zim&acute;ri. Zim&acute;ri, in turn, became father to Mo&acute;za;</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Mo&acute;za, in turn, became father to Bin&acute;e&middot;a, Ra&acute;phah his son, El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;sah his son, A&acute;zel his son.</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">And A&acute;zel had six sons, and these were their names: Az&middot;ri&acute;kam, Bo&acute;che&middot;ru and Ish&acute;ma&middot;el and She&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah and O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah and Ha&acute;nan. All these were the sons of A&acute;zel.</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">And the sons of E&acute;shek his brother were U&acute;lam his firstborn, Je&acute;ush the second and E&middot;liph&acute;e&middot;let the third.</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">And the sons of U&acute;lam came to be valiant, mighty men, bending the bow, and having many sons and grandsons, a hundred and fifty. All these were from the sons of Benjamin.</span>
</p>
</form>

