<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 10:1-14</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="14">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, for their part, made war upon Israel; and the men of Israel went fleeing from before the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines and kept falling slain in Mount Gil&middot;bo&acute;a.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines kept in close range of Saul and his sons; and the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines got to strike down Jon&acute;a&middot;than and A&middot;bin&acute;a&middot;dab and Mal&acute;chi-shu&acute;a, sons of Saul.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And the fighting became heavy against Saul; and those shooting with the bow finally found him, and he got wounded by the shooters.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Then Saul said to his armor-bearer: “Draw your sword and run me through with it, that these uncircumcised men may not come and certainly deal abusively with me.” And his armor-bearer was unwilling, because he was very much afraid. So Saul took the sword and fell upon it.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">When his armor-bearer saw that Saul had died, then he too fell upon the sword and died.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Thus Saul and three sons of his died, and all those of his house died together.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">When all the men of Israel that were in the low plain saw that they had fled and that Saul and his sons had died, then they began to leave their cities and flee; after which the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines came on in and took up dwelling in them.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And it came about the next day that, when the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines came to strip the slain, they got to find Saul and his sons fallen upon Mount Gil&middot;bo&acute;a.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And they proceeded to strip him and take off his head and his armor and send into the land of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines all around to inform their idols and the people.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Finally they put his armor in the house of their god, and his skull they fastened to the house of Da&acute;gon.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And all those of Ja&acute;besh in Gil&acute;e&middot;ad got to hear of all that the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines had done to Saul.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">So all the valiant men rose up and carried off the corpse of Saul and the corpses of his sons and brought them to Ja&acute;besh and buried their bones under the big tree in Ja&acute;besh; and they went fasting for seven days.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Thus Saul died for his unfaithfulness with which he had acted faithlessly against Jehovah concerning the word of Jehovah that he had not kept and also for asking of a spirit medium to make inquiry.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And he did not inquire of Jehovah. Consequently he put him to death and turned the kingship over to David the son of Jes&acute;se.</span>
</p>
</form>

