<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 11:1-47</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="47">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">In time all the Israelites collected themselves together to David at He&acute;bron, saying: “Look! We are your bone and your flesh.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Both yesterday and previously, even while Saul happened to be king, you were the one leading Israel out and bringing it in; and Jehovah your God proceeded to say to you, ‘You yourself will shepherd my people Israel, and you yourself will become leader over my people Israel.’”</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">So all the older men of Israel came to the king at He&acute;bron and David concluded a covenant with them in He&acute;bron before Jehovah; after which they anointed David as king over Israel, according to Jehovah’s word by means of Samuel.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Later David and all Israel went to Jerusalem, that is to say, Je&acute;bus, where the Jeb&acute;u&middot;sites were the inhabitants of the land.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And the inhabitants of Je&acute;bus began to say to David: “You will not come in here.” Just the same, David proceeded to capture the stronghold of Zion, that is to say, the City of David.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">So David said: “Anyone striking the Jeb&acute;u&middot;sites first, he will become head and prince.” And Jo&acute;ab the son of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah got to go up first, and he came to be head.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And David took up dwelling in the place difficult to approach. That is why they called it the City of David.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And he began to build the city all around, from the Mound even to the parts round about, but Jo&acute;ab himself brought to life the rest of the city.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And David went on getting greater and greater, for Jehovah of armies was with him.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Now these are the heads of the mighty men that belonged to David, holding strongly with him in his kingship together with all Israel, to make him king according to Jehovah’s word concerning Israel.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And this is the list of the mighty men that belonged to David: Ja&middot;sho&acute;be&middot;am the son of a Hach&acute;mon&middot;ite, the head of the three. He was brandishing his spear over three hundred slain at one time.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And after him there was El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar the son of Do&acute;do the A&middot;ho&acute;hite. He was among the three mighty men.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">He it was that happened to be with David at Pas-dam&acute;mim, where the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines had gathered themselves together for war. Now there happened to be a tract of the field full of barley, and the people, for their part, had fled because of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">But he took his stand in the middle of the tract and delivered it, and kept striking down the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines, so that Jehovah saved with a great salvation.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And three of the thirty head ones proceeded to go down to the rock, to David at the cave of A&middot;dul&acute;lam, while a camp of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines was camping in the low plain of Reph&acute;a&middot;im.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And David was then in the place hard to approach; and a garrison of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines was then in Beth&acute;le&middot;hem.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">After a while David showed his craving and said: “O that I might have a drink of the water from the cistern of Beth&acute;le&middot;hem, which is at the gate!”</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">At that the three forced their way into the camp of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines and drew water from the cistern of Beth&acute;le&middot;hem, which is at the gate, and came carrying and bringing it to David. And David did not consent to drink it, but poured it out to Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And he went on to say: “It is unthinkable on my part, as regards my God, to do this! Is it the blood of these men that I should drink at the risk of their souls? For it was at the risk of their souls that they brought it.” And he did not consent to drink it. These are the things that the three mighty men did.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">As for A&middot;bish&acute;ai the brother of Jo&acute;ab, he himself became head of the three; and he was brandishing his spear over three hundred slain, and he had a reputation like the three.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">Of the three he was more distinguished than the two others, and he came to be a chief to them; and yet he did not come up to the [first] three.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">As for Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da, the son of a valiant man, who did many deeds in Kab&acute;ze&middot;el, he himself struck down the two [sons] of Ar&acute;i&middot;el of Mo&acute;ab; and he himself descended and struck down a lion inside a waterpit in the day of snowfall.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">And he it was that struck down the Egyptian man, a man of extraordinary size, of five cubits. And in the hand of the Egyptian there was a spear like the beam of loom workers; yet he went on down to him with a rod and snatched the spear away from the Egyptian’s hand and killed him with his own spear.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">These things Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da did, and he had a name among the three mighty men.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">Although he was more distinguished than the thirty, yet to the rank of the [first] three he did not come. However, David put him over his own bodyguard.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">As for the mighty men of the military forces, there were As&acute;a&middot;hel the brother of Jo&acute;ab, El&middot;ha&acute;nan the son of Do&acute;do of Beth&acute;le&middot;hem,</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">Sham&acute;moth the Ha&acute;ro&middot;rite, He&acute;lez the Pel&acute;o&middot;nite,</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">I&acute;ra the son of Ik&acute;kesh the Te&middot;ko&acute;ite, Abi-e&acute;zer the An&acute;a&middot;thoth&middot;ite,</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">Sib&acute;be&middot;cai the Hu&acute;shath&middot;ite, I&acute;lai the A&middot;ho&acute;hite,</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">Ma&acute;ha&middot;rai the Ne&middot;toph&acute;a&middot;thite, He&acute;led the son of Ba&acute;a&middot;nah the Ne&middot;toph&acute;a&middot;thite,</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">I&acute;thai the son of Ri&acute;bai of Gib&acute;e&middot;ah of the sons of Benjamin, Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the Pir&acute;a&middot;thon&middot;ite,</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">Hu&acute;rai from the torrent valleys of Ga&acute;ash, A&middot;bi&acute;el the Ar&acute;bath&middot;ite,</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">Az&acute;ma&middot;veth the Ba&middot;ha&acute;rum&middot;ite, E&middot;li&acute;ah&middot;ba the Sha&middot;al&acute;bo&middot;nite,</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">the sons of Ha&acute;shem the Gi&acute;zo&middot;nite, Jon&acute;a&middot;than the son of Sha&acute;gee the Har&acute;a&middot;rite,</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">A&middot;hi&acute;am the son of Sa&acute;car the Har&acute;a&middot;rite, E&middot;li&acute;phal the son of Ur,</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">He&acute;pher the Me&middot;che&acute;rath&middot;ite, A&middot;hi&acute;jah the Pel&acute;o&middot;nite,</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Hez&acute;ro the Car&acute;mel&middot;ite, Na&acute;a&middot;rai the son of Ez&acute;bai,</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">Joel the brother of Nathan, Mib&acute;har the son of Hag&acute;ri,</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">Ze&acute;lek the Am&acute;mon&middot;ite, Na&acute;ha&middot;rai the Be&middot;roth&acute;ite, the armor-bearer of Jo&acute;ab the son of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah,</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">I&acute;ra the Ith&acute;rite, Ga&acute;reb the Ith&acute;rite,</span> <a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">U&middot;ri&acute;ah the Hit&acute;tite, Za&acute;bad the son of Ah&acute;lai,</span> <a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">Ad&acute;i&middot;na the son of Shi&acute;za the Reu&acute;ben&middot;ite, a head of the Reu&acute;ben&middot;ites, by whom there were thirty;</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">Ha&acute;nan the son of Ma&acute;a&middot;cah, and Josh&acute;a&middot;phat the Mith&acute;nite,</span> <a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">Uz&middot;zi&acute;a the Ash&acute;te&middot;rath&middot;ite, Sha&acute;ma and Je&middot;i&acute;el, the sons of Ho&acute;tham the A&middot;ro&acute;er&middot;ite,</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">Je&middot;di&acute;a&middot;el the son of Shim&acute;ri, and Jo&acute;ha his brother the Ti&acute;zite,</span> <a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">E&acute;li&middot;el the Ma&acute;ha&middot;vite, and Jer&acute;i&middot;bai and Josh&middot;a&middot;vi&acute;ah the sons of El&acute;na&middot;am, and Ith&acute;mah the Mo&acute;ab&middot;ite.</span> <a name="bk47" class="vsAnchor">47</a>
       <span id="vs47">E&acute;li&middot;el and O&acute;bed and Ja&middot;a&middot;si&acute;el the Me&middot;zo&acute;ba&middot;ite.</span>
</p>
</form>

