<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 12:1-40</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="40">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And these are the ones that came to David at Zik&acute;lag while he was still under restrictions because of Saul the son of Kish; and they were among the mighty men, the helpers in the warfare,</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">armed with the bow, using the right hand and using the left hand with stones or with arrows in the bow. They were of the brothers of Saul, of Benjamin.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">There was the head A&middot;hi&middot;e&acute;zer and Jo&acute;ash the sons of She&middot;ma&acute;ah the Gib&acute;e&middot;ath&middot;ite, and Je&acute;zi&middot;el and Pel&acute;et the sons of Az&acute;ma&middot;veth, and Ber&acute;a&middot;cah and Je&acute;hu the An&acute;a&middot;thoth&middot;ite,</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">and Ish&middot;ma&acute;iah the Gib&acute;e&middot;on&middot;ite, a mighty man among the thirty and over the thirty; and Jeremiah and Ja&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;el and Jo&middot;ha&acute;nan and Jo&acute;za&middot;bad the Ge&middot;de&acute;rath&middot;ite,</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">E&middot;lu&acute;zai and Jer&acute;i&middot;moth and Be&middot;a&middot;li&acute;ah and Shem&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah and Sheph&middot;a&middot;ti&acute;ah the Har&acute;i&middot;phite,</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">El&middot;ka&acute;nah and Is&middot;shi&acute;ah and Az&acute;ar&middot;el and Jo&middot;e&acute;zer and Ja&middot;sho&acute;be&middot;am, the Ko&acute;rah&middot;ites,</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">and Jo&middot;e&acute;lah and Zeb&middot;a&middot;di&acute;ah the sons of Je&middot;ro&acute;ham of Ge&acute;dor.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And there were some of the Gad&acute;ites that separated themselves to David’s side at the place difficult to approach in the wilderness, valiant, mighty men, army men for the war, keeping the large shield and the lance ready, whose faces were the faces of lions, and they were like the gazelles upon the mountains for speed.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">E&acute;zer was the head, O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah the second, E&middot;li&acute;ab the third,</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Mish&middot;man&acute;nah the fourth, Jeremiah the fifth,</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">At&acute;tai the sixth, E&acute;li&middot;el the seventh,</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Jo&middot;ha&acute;nan the eighth, El&middot;za&acute;bad the ninth,</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Jeremiah the tenth, Mach&acute;ban&middot;nai the eleventh.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">These were of the sons of Gad, heads of the army. The least one was equal to a hundred, and the greatest to a thousand.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">These are the ones that crossed the Jordan in the first month when it was overflowing all its banks, and they then chased away all those of the low plains, to the east and to the west.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And some of the sons of Benjamin and Judah proceeded to come clear to the place difficult to approach, to David.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Then David went out before them and answered and said to them: “If it is for peace that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> have come to me to help me, my own heart will become at unity with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>. But if it is to betray me to my adversaries when there is no wrong on my palms, let the God of our forefathers see to it and set it in order.”</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And spirit itself enveloped A&middot;ma&acute;sai, the head of the thirty:</span>
</p>

<p class="p"> 
       <span id="vs18-2">“Yours [we are], O David, and with you [we are], O son of Jes&acute;se.<br><span class="z">Peace, peace be yours, and peace to the one helping you,</span><br><span class="z">For your God has helped you.”</span></span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs18-5">So David received them and put them among the heads of the troops.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And there were some of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh that deserted to David when he came with the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines against Saul for battle; but he did not help them, for on counsel the axis lords of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines sent him away, saying: “At the risk of our own heads he will desert to his lord Saul.”</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">When he came to Zik&acute;lag there deserted to him from Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh Ad&acute;nah and Jo&acute;za&middot;bad and Je&middot;di&acute;a&middot;el and Mi&acute;cha&middot;el and Jo&acute;za&middot;bad and E&middot;li&acute;hu and Zil&acute;le&middot;thai, heads of the thousands that belonged to Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And they, for their part, were of help to David against the marauder band, because all of them were mighty men of valor, and they came to be chiefs in the army;</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">for day by day people kept coming to David to help him, until it was a great camp, like the camp of God.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">And these were the numbers of the heads of those equipped for the army that came to David at He&acute;bron to turn the kingship of Saul over to him according to Jehovah’s order.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">The sons of Judah carrying the large shield and the lance were six thousand eight hundred, equipped for the army.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">Of the sons of Sim&acute;e&middot;on the mighty men of valor of the army were seven thousand one hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">Of the sons of the Levites four thousand six hundred.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da was the leader [of the sons] of Aaron, and with him there were three thousand seven hundred.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">Also Za&acute;dok a young man, mighty in valor, and the house of his forefathers, twenty-two chiefs.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And of the sons of Benjamin, the brothers of Saul, there were three thousand, and up till then the greater number of them were keeping strict watch of the house of Saul.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">And of the sons of E&acute;phra&middot;im there were twenty thousand eight hundred, mighty men of valor, men of fame, by the house of their forefathers.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And of the half tribe of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh there were eighteen thousand that had been designated by name to come to make David king.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And of the sons of Is&acute;sa&middot;char having a knowledge of how to discern the times to know what Israel ought to do, there were two hundred head ones of theirs, and all their brothers were at their orders.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">Of Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun those going out to the army, drawing up in battle formation with all the weapons of war, there were fifty thousand, and for flocking together [to David] they were not of a double heart.</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">And of Naph&acute;ta&middot;li there were a thousand chiefs, and with them with the large shield and the spear there were thirty-seven thousand.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">And of the Dan&acute;ites those drawing up in battle formation were twenty-eight thousand six hundred.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">And of Ash&acute;er those going out to the army for drawing up in battle formation were forty thousand.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">And from across the Jordan of the Reu&acute;ben&middot;ites and the Gad&acute;ites and the half tribe of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh with all the weapons of the military army there were a hundred and twenty thousand.</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">All these were men of war, flocking together in battle line; with a complete heart they came to He&acute;bron to make David king over all Israel; and also all the remainder of Israel were of one heart for making David king.</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">And they continued there with David three days, eating and drinking, for their brothers had made preparation for them.</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">And also those near to them, as far as Is&acute;sa&middot;char and Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun and Naph&acute;ta&middot;li, were bringing food upon asses and upon camels and upon mules and upon cattle, eatables of flour, cakes of pressed figs and cakes of raisins and wine and oil and cattle and sheep in great quantity, for there was rejoicing in Israel.</span>
</p>
</form>

