<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 13:1-14</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="14">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And David proceeded to consult with the chiefs of the thousands and of the hundreds and with every leader;</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">and David went on to say to all the congregation of Israel: “If it seems good to <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> and it is acceptable with Jehovah our God, let us send to our brothers that are left over in all the lands of Israel and with them [to] the priests and the Levites in their cities with pasture grounds, that they may collect themselves together to us.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And let us bring the ark of our God around to ourselves.” For they had not cared for it in the days of Saul.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">So all the congregation said to do that way, for the thing seemed right in the eyes of all the people.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Accordingly David congregated all Israel from the river of Egypt as far as the entering of Ha&acute;math, to bring the ark of the [true] God from Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And David and all Israel proceeded to go up to Ba&acute;al&middot;ah, to Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-je&acute;a&middot;rim, which belongs to Judah, to bring up from there the ark of the [true] God, Jehovah, sitting on the cherubs, where [his] name is called on.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">However, they had the ark of the [true] God ride upon a new wagon from the house of A&middot;bin&acute;a&middot;dab, and Uz&acute;zah and A&middot;hi&acute;o were leading the wagon.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And David and all Israel were celebrating before the [true] God with full power and with songs and with harps and with stringed instruments and with tambourines and with cymbals and with trumpets.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And they came gradually as far as the threshing floor of Chi&acute;don, and Uz&acute;zah now thrust his hand out to grab hold of the Ark, for the bulls nearly caused an upset.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">At that Jehovah’s anger blazed against Uz&acute;zah, so that he struck him down because he had thrust his hand out upon the Ark, and he died there before God.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And David became angry because Jehovah had broken through in a rupture against Uz&acute;zah; and that place came to be called Pe&acute;rez-uz&acute;zah down to this day.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And David became afraid of the [true] God on that day, saying: “How shall I bring the ark of the [true] God to me?”</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And David did not remove the Ark to himself at the City of David, but he carried it aside to the house of O&acute;bed-e&acute;dom the Git&acute;tite.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And the ark of the [true] God kept dwelling with the household of O&acute;bed-e&acute;dom, at his house three months; and Jehovah kept blessing the household of O&acute;bed-e&acute;dom and all that was his.</span>
</p>
</form>

