<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 15:1-29</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="29">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And he continued building houses for himself in the City of David; and he went on to prepare a place for the ark of the [true] God and pitch a tent for it.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">It was then that David said: “No one is to carry the ark of the [true] God but the Levites, for they are the ones whom Jehovah has chosen to carry the ark of Jehovah and to minister to him to time indefinite.”</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Then David congregated all Israel at Jerusalem to bring the ark of Jehovah up to its place that he had prepared for it.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And David proceeded to gather the sons of Aaron and the Levites;</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">of the sons of Ko&acute;hath, U&middot;ri&acute;el the chief and his brothers, a hundred and twenty;</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">of the sons of Me&middot;rar&acute;i, A&middot;sai&acute;ah the chief and his brothers, two hundred and twenty;</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">of the sons of Ger&acute;shom, Joel the chief and his brothers, a hundred and thirty;</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">of the sons of E&middot;li&middot;za&acute;phan, She&middot;mai&acute;ah the chief and his brothers, two hundred;</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">of the sons of He&acute;bron, E&acute;li&middot;el the chief and his brothers, eighty;</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">of the sons of Uz&acute;zi&middot;el, Am&middot;min&acute;a&middot;dab the chief and his brothers, a hundred and twelve.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Furthermore, David called Za&acute;dok and A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar the priests, and the Levites U&middot;ri&acute;el, A&middot;sai&acute;ah and Joel, She&middot;mai&acute;ah and E&acute;li&middot;el and Am&middot;min&acute;a&middot;dab,</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">and he went on to say to them: “Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> are the heads of the fathers of the Levites. Sanctify yourselves, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> and <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> brothers, and <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must bring the ark of Jehovah the God of Israel up to the place that I have prepared for it.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Because at the first time <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> did not, Jehovah our God broke through against us, for we did not search after him according to the custom.”</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">So the priests and the Levites sanctified themselves to bring up the ark of Jehovah the God of Israel.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">Then the sons of the Levites began to carry the ark of the [true] God, just as Moses had commanded by Jehovah’s word, upon their shoulders with the rods upon them.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">David now said to the chiefs of the Levites to station their brothers the singers with the instruments of song, stringed instruments and harps and cymbals, playing aloud to cause a sound of rejoicing to arise.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Accordingly the Levites stationed He&acute;man the son of Joel and, of his brothers, A&acute;saph the son of Ber&middot;e&middot;chi&acute;ah; and, of the sons of Me&middot;rar&acute;i their brothers, E&acute;than the son of Kush&middot;a&acute;iah;</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">and with them their brothers of the second division, Zech&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah, Ben and Ja&middot;a&acute;zi&middot;el and She&middot;mir&acute;a&middot;moth and Je&middot;hi&acute;el and Un&acute;ni, E&middot;li&acute;ab and Be&middot;nai&acute;ah and Ma&middot;a&middot;sei&acute;ah and Mat&middot;ti&middot;thi&acute;ah and E&middot;liph&acute;e&middot;le&middot;hu and Mik&middot;ne&acute;iah, and O&acute;bed-e&acute;dom and Je&middot;i&acute;el the gatekeepers,</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">and the singers He&acute;man, A&acute;saph and E&acute;than, with the copper cymbals to play aloud;</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">and Zech&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah and A&acute;zi&middot;el and She&middot;mir&acute;a&middot;moth and Je&middot;hi&acute;el and Un&acute;ni and E&middot;li&acute;ab and Ma&middot;a&middot;sei&acute;ah and Be&middot;nai&acute;ah with stringed instruments tuned to Al&acute;a&middot;moth,</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">and Mat&middot;ti&middot;thi&acute;ah and E&middot;liph&acute;e&middot;le&middot;hu and Mik&middot;ne&acute;iah and O&acute;bed-e&acute;dom and Je&middot;i&acute;el and Az&middot;a&middot;zi&acute;ah with harps tuned to Shem&acute;i&middot;nith, to act as directors;</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">and Chen&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah the chief of the Levites in carrying, he giving instruction in carrying, for he was expert;</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">and Ber&middot;e&middot;chi&acute;ah and El&middot;ka&acute;nah the gatekeepers for the Ark;</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">and Sheb&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah and Josh&acute;a&middot;phat and Ne&middot;than&acute;el and A&middot;ma&acute;sai and Zech&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah and Be&middot;nai&acute;ah and E&middot;li&middot;e&acute;zer the priests loudly sounding the trumpets before the ark of the [true] God, and O&acute;bed-e&acute;dom and Je&middot;hi&acute;ah the gatekeepers for the Ark.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And David and the older men of Israel and the chiefs of the thousands came to be the ones walking along to bring up the ark of the covenant of Jehovah from the house of O&acute;bed-e&acute;dom with rejoicing.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And it came about when the [true] God helped the Levites while carrying the ark of the covenant of Jehovah that they proceeded to sacrifice seven young bulls and seven rams.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And David was dressed in a sleeveless coat of fine fabric, and also all the Levites carrying the Ark and the singers and Chen&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah the chief of the carrying by the singers; but upon David there was an eph&acute;od of linen.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And all the Israelites were bringing up the ark of the covenant of Jehovah with joyful shouting and with the sounding of the horn and with trumpets and with cymbals, playing aloud on stringed instruments and harps.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And it came about that, when the ark of the covenant of Jehovah came as far as the City of David, Mi&acute;chal, Saul’s daughter, herself looked down through the window and got to see King David skipping about and celebrating; and she began to despise him in her heart.</span>
</p>
</form>

