<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 18:1-17</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="17">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about afterward that David proceeded to strike down the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines and subdue them and take Gath and its dependent towns out of the hand of the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Then he struck Mo&acute;ab down, and the Mo&acute;ab&middot;ites came to be David’s servants bearing tribute.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And David went on to strike down Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer the king of Zo&acute;bah at Ha&acute;math as he was going his way to set up his control at the river Eu&middot;phra&acute;tes.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Further, David captured from him a thousand chariots and seven thousand horsemen and twenty thousand men on foot. Then David hamstrung all the chariot horses, but he let a hundred chariot horses of them remain.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">When Syria of Damascus came to help Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer the king of Zo&acute;bah, David went striking down among the Syrians twenty-two thousand men.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">After that David put [garrisons] in Syria of Damascus, and the Syrians came to be David’s servants bearing tribute. And Jehovah kept giving salvation to David wherever he went.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Moreover, David took the circular shields of gold that happened to be on the servants of Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer and brought them to Jerusalem.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And from Tib&acute;hath and Cun, cities of Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer, David took very much copper. With it Sol&acute;o&middot;mon made the copper sea and the pillars and the copper utensils.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">When To&acute;u the king of Ha&acute;math heard that David had struck down all the military force of Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer the king of Zo&acute;bah,</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">he immediately sent Ha&middot;do&acute;ram his son to King David to ask him about his welfare and congratulate him over the fact that he had fought against Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer so that he struck him down, (for Had&middot;ad&middot;e&acute;zer had become trained in warfare against To&acute;u,) and [there were with him] all sorts of articles of gold and silver and copper.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">These also King David sanctified to Jehovah together with the silver and the gold that he had carried off from all the nations, from E&acute;dom and from Mo&acute;ab and from the sons of Am&acute;mon and from the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines and from Am&acute;a&middot;lek.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">As for A&middot;bish&acute;ai the son of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah, he struck down the E&acute;dom&middot;ites in the Valley of Salt, eighteen thousand.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">So he put garrisons in E&acute;dom, and all the E&acute;dom&middot;ites came to be David’s servants. And Jehovah kept saving David wherever he went.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And David continued to reign over all Israel, and he was continually rendering judicial decision and righteousness for all his people.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And Jo&acute;ab the son of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah was over the army, and Je&middot;hosh&acute;a&middot;phat the son of A&middot;hi&acute;lud was recorder.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And Za&acute;dok the son of A&middot;hi&acute;tub and A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech the son of A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar were priests, and Shav&acute;sha was secretary.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da was over the Cher&acute;e&middot;thites and the Pel&acute;e&middot;thites; and the sons of David were the first in position at the side of the king.</span>
</p>
</form>

