<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 20:1-8</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="8">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about at the time of the year’s return, at the time that kings sally forth, that Jo&acute;ab proceeded to lead the combat force of the army and lay the land of the sons of Am&acute;mon in ruin and to come and besiege Rab&acute;bah, while David was dwelling in Jerusalem; and Jo&acute;ab went on to strike Rab&acute;bah and throw it down.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">But David took the crown of Mal&acute;cam off its head, and found it to be a talent of gold in weight, and in it there were precious stones; and it came to be on David’s head. And the spoil of the city that he brought out was very much.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And the people that were in it he brought out, and he kept them employed at sawing stones and at sharp instruments of iron and at axes; and that was the way David proceeded to do to all the cities of the sons of Am&acute;mon. Finally David and all the people returned to Jerusalem.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And it came about after this that war began breaking out at Ge&acute;zer with the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines. It was then that Sib&acute;be&middot;cai the Hu&acute;shath&middot;ite struck down Sip&acute;pai of those born of the Reph&acute;a&middot;im, so that they were subdued.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And there came to be war again with the Phi&middot;lis&acute;tines; and El&middot;ha&acute;nan the son of Ja&acute;ir got to strike down Lah&acute;mi the brother of Go&middot;li&acute;ath the Git&acute;tite, the shaft of whose spear was like the beam of loom workers.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And there came to be war again at Gath, when there happened to be a man of extraordinary size whose fingers and toes were in sixes, twenty-four; and he, too, had been born to the Reph&acute;a&middot;im.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And he kept taunting Israel. Finally Jon&acute;a&middot;than the son of Shim&acute;e&middot;a the brother of David struck him down.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">These were the ones that had been born to the Reph&acute;a&middot;im in Gath; and they came to fall by the hand of David and by the hand of his servants.</span>
</p>
</form>

