<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Chronicles 24:1-31</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="29">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="31">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Now the sons of Aaron had their divisions. The sons of Aaron were Na&acute;dab and A&middot;bi&acute;hu, El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar and Ith&acute;a&middot;mar.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">However, Na&acute;dab and A&middot;bi&acute;hu died before their father, and they did not happen to have any sons, but El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar and Ith&acute;a&middot;mar continued to act as priests.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And David, and Za&acute;dok from the sons of El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar, and A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech from the sons of Ith&acute;a&middot;mar proceeded to make divisions of them for their office in their service.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">But the sons of El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar were found to be more numerous in headmen than the sons of Ith&acute;a&middot;mar. So they distributed them to the sons of El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar, as heads for [their] paternal houses, sixteen, and to the sons of Ith&acute;a&middot;mar, [as heads] for their paternal houses, eight.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Further, they distributed them by lots, these along with those, for there had to be chiefs of the holy place and chiefs of the [true] God from the sons of El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar and from the sons of Ith&acute;a&middot;mar.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Then She&middot;mai&acute;ah the son of Ne&middot;than&acute;el the secretary of the Levites wrote them down before the king and the princes and Za&acute;dok the priest and A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech the son of A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar and the heads of the fathers of the priests and of the Levites, one paternal house being picked out for El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar and one being picked out for Ith&acute;a&middot;mar.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And the lot proceeded to come out: the first for Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;rib; for Je&middot;da&acute;iah the second,</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">for Ha&acute;rim the third, for Se&middot;o&acute;rim the fourth,</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">for Mal&middot;chi&acute;jah the fifth, for Mij&acute;a&middot;min the sixth,</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">for Hak&acute;koz the seventh, for A&middot;bi&acute;jah the eighth,</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">for Jesh&acute;u&middot;a the ninth, for Shec&middot;a&middot;ni&acute;ah the tenth,</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">for E&middot;li&acute;a&middot;shib the eleventh, for Ja&acute;kim the twelfth,</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">for Hup&acute;pah the thirteenth, for Je&middot;sheb&acute;e&middot;ab the fourteenth,</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">for Bil&acute;gah the fifteenth, for Im&acute;mer the sixteenth,</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">for He&acute;zir the seventeenth, for Hap&acute;piz&middot;zez the eighteenth,</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">for Peth&middot;a&middot;hi&acute;ah the nineteenth, for Je&middot;hez&acute;kel the twentieth,</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">for Ja&acute;chin the twenty-first, for Ga&acute;mul the twenty-second,</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">for De&middot;la&acute;iah the twenty-third, for Ma&middot;a&middot;zi&acute;ah the twenty-fourth.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">These were their offices for their service, to come into the house of Jehovah according to their due right by the hand of Aaron their forefather, just as Jehovah the God of Israel had commanded him.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And of the sons of Le&acute;vi that were left over, of the sons of Am&acute;ram there was Shu&acute;ba&middot;el; of the sons of Shu&acute;ba&middot;el, Jeh&middot;de&acute;iah;</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">of Re&middot;ha&middot;bi&acute;ah: of the sons of Re&middot;ha&middot;bi&acute;ah, Is&middot;shi&acute;ah the head;</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">of the Iz&acute;har&middot;ites, She&middot;lo&acute;moth; of the sons of She&middot;lo&acute;moth, Ja&acute;hath;</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">and the sons [of He&acute;bron], Je&middot;ri&acute;ah the head, Am&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah the second, Ja&middot;ha&middot;zi&acute;el the third, Jek&middot;a&middot;me&acute;am the fourth.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">The sons of Uz&acute;zi&middot;el, Mi&acute;cah; of the sons of Mi&acute;cah, Sha&acute;mir.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">The brother of Mi&acute;cah was Is&middot;shi&acute;ah; of the sons of Is&middot;shi&acute;ah, Zech&middot;a&middot;ri&acute;ah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">The sons of Me&middot;rar&acute;i were Mah&acute;li and Mu&acute;shi; the sons of Ja&middot;a&middot;zi&acute;ah, Be&acute;no.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">The sons of Me&middot;rar&acute;i: Of Ja&middot;a&middot;zi&acute;ah, Be&acute;no and Sho&acute;ham and Zac&acute;cur and Ib&acute;ri.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">Of Mah&acute;li, El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar, who did not come to have any sons.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">Of Kish: the sons of Kish were Je&middot;rah&acute;me&middot;el.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">And the sons of Mu&acute;shi were Mah&acute;li and E&acute;der and Jer&acute;i&middot;moth.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs30-2">These were the sons of the Levites by their paternal houses.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And they themselves also proceeded to cast lots exactly as their brothers the sons of Aaron did before David the king and Za&acute;dok and A&middot;him&acute;e&middot;lech and the heads of the paternal houses of the priests and of the Levites. As respects paternal houses, the head one was exactly as his younger brother.</span>
</p>
</form>

